  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: when you set custom time and go back to status app, \"Connecting to peers\" error appears and you cannot send/receive messages for a while.\r\nCan be reproduced on Android, desktop, on IOS several times I saw the same issue, but sometimes it is just unusable until restarting (history for chats is missed, you cannot send message. Video is [here](https://monosnap.com/file/X1vojOH6aAi2dJDG6jZYsHEFfTLjsS) )\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\ncan send / receive messages and browse history or app requires restarting\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\"Connecting to peers\" error\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Join any public channel\r\n- Open time preferences\r\n- Change time\r\n- Open Status again (from background)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: nightly 19/10/2018\r\n* Operating System: Android 7.0, iOS 11.4, Mac OSx 10.13.6\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n* StatusIm.log (desktop): [StatusIm_time.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2495860/StatusIm_time.log)\r\n* Geth.log  (desktop): [geth_time.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2495854/geth_time.log)\r\n* Video (IOS): [IOS](https://monosnap.com/file/X1vojOH6aAi2dJDG6jZYsHEFfTLjsS)\r\n* Video [Android, after setting time](https://monosnap.com/file/YYOl7QjOekD95MbSS8E9oc4Vi5YwJk)\r\n",
